    "Audibert and Bousquet studied a PAC-Bayes version of the chaining argument (Audibert and Bousquet, 2007).",
    "See also versions based on Mutual Information bounds (Asadi et al., 2018; Clerico et al., 2022c).",
    "Finally, Kakade et al. (2008) and Yang et al. (2019) proved PAC-Bayes bounds using Rademacher complexity.",
    "More generally, Catoni developped recently a technique to prove upper bound on the risk of non-Bayesian estimators that relies on PAC-Bayes bounds.",
